                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "An empty label or a button without a value is the same as a doorbell without a name plate. ;)\r\nSet always a text\/value for the button and a blind visitors will thank you! (screen reader)\r\n\r\nUse CSS:\r\n{code:title=Example}\r\ninput[type='reset'] {\r\n    text-indent: -9999px;\r\n    width: 100px;\r\n    background-image: \u2026\r\n}\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-04-15T16:16:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-04-15T16:16:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/45881",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fumanchu182",
                        "name": "fumanchu182",
                        "displayName": "Anthony W.",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I would have to disagree.  That is why the alt attribute is allowed on input elements for forms.  http:\/\/www.w3.org\/QA\/Tips\/altAttribute.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fumanchu182",
                        "name": "fumanchu182",
                        "displayName": "Anthony W.",
                        "active": true
